  "explanation": "The defendant committed a serious breach of trust by embezzling $25,000 from their employer in their capacity as an accountant. However, several mitigating factors warrant a lenient sentence, including the lack of any prior criminal record and the voluntary partial restitution of the stolen funds before sentencing. A brief period of incarceration of 3 months is sufficient to satisfy the goals of deterrence and accountability, followed by a period of supervised release and a requirement to pay the remaining restitution.",
